Mike Ellis, the finance director in 2004, alerted the HBOS board to the FSA’s concern that the bank was growing too fast
Patrick Hosking
Financial Editor
Published at 12:01AM, November 13 2012
The board of HBOS was told four years before the bank’s collapse that the City watchdog viewed its growth strategy as “an accident waiting to happen”, according to evidence put before a parliamentary hearing yesterday.
Board minutes seen by the Parliamentary Commission on Banking Standards revealed how Mike Ellis, the finance director in 2004, had alerted the board to the Financial Services Authority’s concern that HBOS was growing too fast.
